    • Method Detail

      • write

        <K,V> void write(String namedOutput,
               K key,
               V value)
           throws IOException,
                  InterruptedException
        Write key and value to the named output Dataset. This method must only be used if the MapReduce writes to more than one output. If there is a single output, write(Object, Object) must be used, or else data may not be written correctly.
        Parameters:
        namedOutput - the name of the output Dataset
        key - the key
        value - the value
        Throws:
        IOException
        InterruptedException

      • write

        void write(KEYOUT key,
         VALUEOUT value)
           throws IOException,
                  InterruptedException
        Write key and value to the hadoop context. This method must only be used in the MapReduce writes to a single output. If there is more than one outputs, write(String, Object, Object) must be used.
        Parameters:
        key - the key
        value - the value
        Throws:
        IOException
        InterruptedException

      • getSpecification

        MapReduceSpecification getSpecification()
        Returns:
        The specification used to configure this MapReduce job instance.

      • getLogicalStartTime

        long getLogicalStartTime()
        Returns the logical start time of this MapReduce job. Logical start time is the time when this MapReduce job is supposed to start if this job is started by the scheduler. Otherwise it would be the current time when the job runs.
        Returns:
        Time in milliseconds since epoch time (00:00:00 January 1, 1970 UTC).

      • getHadoopContext

        <T> T getHadoopContext()
        Returns the Hadoop context object for the task.

      • getWorkflowToken

        @Nullable
WorkflowToken getWorkflowToken()
        Returns:
        the WorkflowToken associated with the current Workflow, if the MapReduce program is executed as a part of the Workflow; returns null otherwise.
